The Oluwo of Iwoland, Oba Abdulrasheed Adewale Akanbi’s marriage to his wife, Chanel Chin has crashed. This was announced in a statement signed by the monarch’s Chief Press Secretary (CPS), Mr Alli Ibraheem However, the reason for the separation between the traditional ruler and his ex-wife, a Jamaican, who had a boy named Oduduwa for him could not be ascertained. Chin, henceforth would be referred to as an ex-Queen of Iwoland. The statement read: “This is to inform the general public, most especially friends and associates of the Oluwo of Iwoland, His Imperial Majesty, Oba (Dr) Abdulrosheed Adewale Akanbi, Telu I, that Ms Chanel Chin is an ex-queen of his majesty. “This information is necessary for the attention of the general public to avoid representation on proxy or accordance of respect attached to the sacred stool of Oluwo to her. “For personal irreconcilable differences, Chanel Chin ceases to be his Majesty’s queen. We equally enjoin the public to disregard any business transaction or request with her using the office of his majesty. “We wish her the best in her new journey.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.